            "answer_text": "If I started listing down the reasons why I love the song, \"California\" as a town would not even appear in the 100th place. The song has got little to do with the city itself. Rather, they talk about a hotel which is simply named as \"Hotel California\".  So why are people crazy about the song?  Unique, thought provoking lyrics. It's not your typical \"love you love me hate me\" song. Soothing music; especially in the live version featured in the album \"Hell Freezes Over\". Excellent introductory guitar solo. In fact, all the guitar solos in the song are awesome. The easy listening flow of the song. It's a long song, but you never feel bored while listening to it. Something intriguing is always coming up. There are many more reasons, but these are the ones that came to me right away. ",
