            "answer_text": "Because Hotel California is an extremely well-composed epic. It is considered a timeless classic rock tune for a number of reasons, and some of them that I can think of include: Its highly recognisable guitar intro, which is a common feature found in pretty much majority of all rock classicsGreat lyrics that are non-cliched and open to your own interpretation in natureFantastic lead vocals by Don Henley, who sang with a great balance of urgency and \u2018laid back\u2019-ness at the same timeAmazing outro guitar solo played by both Joe Walsh and Don Felder, which is also one of the greatest lead guitar moments in music history",
